Installation (to an existing project):

•	composer require --dev zfcampus/zf-asset-manager (required for rendering the admin ui)
•	composer require zfcampus/zf-apigility
•	composer require --dev zfcampus/zf-apigility-admin
•	composer require --dev zfcampus/zf-development-mode

•	Ensure that development mode is enabled
(“.\vendor\bin\zf-development-mode status” should return ENABLED. If not then run “.\vendor\bin\zf-development-mode enable”)


Authentication and Authorization using doctrine:

- Oauth doctrine must be installed:
composer require api-skeletons/zf-oauth2-doctrine
- Copy the file at vendor/api-skeletons/zf-oauth2-doctrine/config/oauth2.doctrine-orm.global.php.dist to config/autoload directory.

Update the database schema to get the tables

User entity should implement ZF\OAuth2\Doctrine\Entity\UserInterface and should implement getArrayCopy() function

'zf-mvc-auth' => array(
    'authentication' => array(
        'adapters' => array(
            'oauth2_doctrine' => array(
                'adapter' => 'ZF\\MvcAuth\\Authentication\\OAuth2Adapter',
                'storage' => array(
                    'storage' => 'oauth2.doctrineadapter.default',
                    'route' => '/oauth',
                ),
            ),
        ),
    ),
),

For the Authorization header to be accessible, the following line should be added in .htaccess file just after the RewriteEngine On line:
        “RewriteRule .* - [E=HTTP_AUTHORIZATION:%{HTTP:Authorization}]”


